    "body": "Fixes #5952.\r\n\r\nLooking at the OpenMP documentation (https://www.openmp.org/spec-html/5.0/openmpsu35.html#x55-880002.6.1) it says\r\n\r\n> if a num_threads clause exists\r\n> then let ThreadsRequested be the value of the num_threads clause expression;\r\n> else let ThreadsRequested = value of the first element of nthreads-var;\r\n\r\nwhere the first element of `nthreads-var` is specified elsewhere as the result of `omp_get_max_threads()`.\r\n\r\nSo it's reasonably easy for Cython to work out what would have happened if we weren't generating `num_threads(...)`.\r\n\r\nI've used `num_threads=0` as the special value, but equally `-1` or `None` could be considered (I think `None` would be harder to implment though).  Alternatively, if we didn't want to build the special behaviour into Cython we could just document this as a pattern, but it's sufficiently simple that I think it's worth doing ourselves.",
    "closed_at": null,
