                "message": "Make it easy to set parallel/prange to use default number of threads\n\nFixes #5952.\n\nLooking at the OpenMP documentation (https://www.openmp.org/spec-html/5.0/openmpsu35.html#x55-880002.6.1)\nit says\n\n> if a num_threads clause exists\n> then let ThreadsRequested be the value of the num_threads clause expression;\n> else let ThreadsRequested = value of the first element of nthreads-var;\n\nwhere the first element of `nthreads-var` is specified elsewhere\nas the result of `omp_get_max_threads()`.\n\nSo it's reasonably easy for Cython to work out what would have\nhappened if we weren't generating `num_threads(...)`.\n\nI've used `num_threads=0` as the special value, but equally\n`-1` or `None` could be considered (I think `None` would be\nharder to implment though).  Alternatively, if we didn't\nwant to build the special behaviour into Cython we could just\ndocument this as a pattern, but it's sufficiently simple\nthat I think it's worth doing ourselves.",
